pd_0_com_1text: My deepest condolences, Lady Hot Air Balloon!
pd_0_com_2text: May the soul of the Lord find peace in the great balloon heaven.
pd_1_com_2text: Is there anything else I can do for you as mistress of the house?
pd_2_com_0text: Actually, I'd like to ask you a few questions, if you don't mind.
pd_4_com_0text: [What should I ask the lady about?]
pd_6_com_2text: I don't have any more questions.
pd_7_com_0text: "Signora hot air balloon, I love you and cannot bear to live another day without you."
pd_9_com_0text: Do you know these phrases? This is the content of a love letter addressed to you. Could you tell me what you know about it, Lady Hot Air Balloon?
pd_10_com_0text: Are you implying that I wasn't faithful to my husband?!?
pd_10_com_1text: My husband is hardly dead and people are already discrediting me.
pd_10_com_2text: What an outrage! What a disgrace!
pd_11_com_0text: Please calm down, lady hot-air balloon. Nobody is trying to denounce you. But I thought that maybe the author of this letter could also be the murderer of Lord Zeppelin.
pd_11_com_1text: All right, I understand that you have absolutely nothing to do with this and know nothing about it. I will make sure that no one will bother you anymore.
pd_11_com_2text: [Her eccentric reaction shows she's trying to hide something from me.]
pd_11_com_3text: [Maybe I'll make progress if I can find out who wrote this letter.]
pd_13_com_0text: What can you tell me about Detective ShAIRlock Holmes?
pd_14_com_0text: He's a detective. Probably the best detective in Balloonia who has solved many difficult cases.
pd_14_com_1text: But why are you asking me about yourself, Mr. Holmes?
pd_15_com_0text: The general is an old friend of Lord Zeppelin.
pd_15_com_4text: I am sorry. The general was an old friend of Lord Zeppelin.
pd_15_com_5text: They knew each other from some war or something. I don't know, I never listened.
pd_15_com_6text: I never really had anything to do with him before. But I often meet with his wife. Opera, theatre, painting, fashion shows and of course in the cafe.
pd_15_com_7text: She has such an exquisite taste in the selection of her dresses.
pd_15_com_8text: But lately she rarely leaves her house and when she does, she wears fashion from the last years.
pd_15_com_9text: I wonder if she and the General are in financial distress.
pd_15_com_10text: Oh, forgive me, I shouldn't tattle about other people's problems.
pd_16_com_0text: [Interesting! The general has a dire financial problem.]
pd_16_com_1text: Not at all! Your help was of the utmost significance for my investigation.
pd_16_com_2text: I am deeply indebted to you.
pd_17_com_0text: Tee-hee. I helped the great ShAIRlock Holmes with his latest case. I can't wait to tell my friends about this.
pd_18_com_0text: Lord Zeppelin was a very loving, reliable, warm-hearted, careful, kind, patient, ambitious, consistent, responsible, hard-working, focused, accurate, honest, truthful, intelligent,
pd_18_com_1text: functional, balanced, confident, courageous, detail-oriented, respecting, committed, faithful, humble, adaptable, well-bred, curious, grateful, reasonable, educated and honest balloon.
pd_19_com_0text: Yes, it must be a great loss for you.
pd_21_com_0text: I am sure that he took good care of you and that you do not have to worry about your well-being after his death.
pd_22_com_0text: Yes, I am the sole heiress of his family wealth.
pd_22_com_1text: That makes me one of the richest balloons in Balloonia.
pd_22_com_2text: But is that important right now?
pd_23_com_0text: [So she's the sole heir? It is an enormous fortune. But is that reason enough for her to murder her husband?]
pd_23_com_1text: Of course not, lady hot-air balloon. But it reassures me to know that at least you don't have to worry about your future.
pd_24_com_0text: I appreciate your concern for me, Mr Holmes.
pd_25_com_0text: May I ask you something else?
pd_25_com_1text: Did Lord Zeppelin have any medical conditions?
pd_26_com_0text: Yes, he had a very high air pressure for many years, but he took medication against it.
pd_27_com_0text: And where did he keep these medications?
pd_28_com_1text: Does this have something to do with the murder?
pd_29_com_0text: [That means the lady had access to the medicine used to murder the lord.]
pd_30_com_0text: [What if she had given the medicine to the cook and asked him to do the deed as a proof of love?]
pd_31_com_0text: [Assuming the general found the medication while searching the Lord's study, he would then also have had access to the murder weapon.]
pd_32_com_0text: Don't worry too much about it. I'm just trying to get a grasp of the case.
pd_33_com_0text: [The new last will is my only solid clue, I can't risk her getting her hands on it.]
pd_33_com_1text: [For now, I think it'd be better if she didn't know I have the will.]
pd_34_com_0text: He cooks some really good meals, I like his accent and have known him for years.
pd_35_com_0text: Well, that's a weird question, I'm just me, the Lady of the House.
